DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday\, April 15\, from 4–7 PM at Whispering Vine South Creek for a tasting featuring the elegant and expressive wines of Stags’ Leap Winery\, a Napa Valley producer known for balancing power\, polish\, and classic varietal character.\nTasting Fee: $35 (Buy a bottle from the tasting and your fee is refunded)\nFeatured Wines:\n• Stags’ Leap Winery The Investor Red Wine 2020 – A plush and layered blend with ripe red berries\, dark plum\, wild lavender\, mocha\, and a long\, spiced finish.\n• Stags’ Leap Winery Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 – 93 pts James Suckling – Silky and aromatic with red berries\, sweet oak\, violet\, tea leaf\, and a polished finish.\n• Stags’ Leap Winery Petite Sirah 2021 – 92 pts Wine Enthusiast – Vibrant and beautifully structured with blackberry pie\, boysenberry\, thyme\, and firm\, elegant tannins.\n• Stags’ Leap Winery Sauvignon Blanc 2023 – 90 pts Wine Enthusiast – Bright and refreshing with nectarine\, tropical fruit\, citrus\, and a lively\, mouthwatering finish.\nDiscover the depth and finesse of Stags’ Leap Winery—buy a bottle and your tasting is free.
LOCATION:85 Foothill Rd Ste 1 Reno\, NV 89511
SUMMARY:Stags’ Leap Winery Tasting
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR